# AI Trust Case Studies

> A collection of real-world AI case studies exploring fairness, transparency, accountability, human oversight, and other core principles of Trustworthy AI.

---

##  About

This repository presents a collection of carefully researched case studies on real-world Artificial Intelligence (AI) systems. Each case study analyzes how AI was applied, the challenges encountered, the Trustworthy AI principles involved, and the lessons learned.

The purpose of this repository is to help students, researchers, and AI enthusiasts understand how Trustworthy AI concepts are applied in real-world scenarios through detailed and evidence-based analysis.

---

## Case Studies

- **Amazon AI Recruiting Tool (2018)** – AI Bias and Fairness in Recruitment
- **COMPAS Recidivism Algorithm** – Fairness, Transparency, and Accountability
- **Microsoft Tay Chatbot (2016)** – AI Safety and Content Moderation
- **ChatGPT Hallucinations** – Reliability, Explainability, and Human Oversight
- **Tesla Autopilot** – Human–AI Interaction, Automation, and Safety

